%I A394868 #17 Apr 19 2026 21:56:27
%S A394868 0,3,4,12,12,20,20,28
%N A394868 a(n) is the final number of steps reached by Alice and Bob, in the optimization game on an n X n grid described in comments.
%C A394868 On an n X n grid, Alice and Bob play an optimization game: They take turns moving a piece that starts in the bottom left corner. Alice moves first. Alice can move the piece to a diagonally adjacent square, and Bob can move it to a horizontally or vertically adjacent square. Neither player can move the piece off the board or to a square it has previously been on. Alice wants to move as many steps as possible, while Bob wants to prevent her from doing so.
%H A394868 Yifan Xie, <a href="/A394868/a394868_1.py.txt">Python program</a>
%e A394868 For n = 3, Alice's strategy is to move the piece to wherever has space. Bob always has space to move after Alice's second diagonal move, so Alice can guarantee at least 4 steps.
%e A394868 Bob's strategy is to move the piece into the corner on his second move, since the piece must be in a grid adjacent to the center, after Alice's second move. Since the center has been moved to, Alice has no way to move then. Therefore, Bob can guarantee at most 4 steps, hence a(3) = 4.
%o A394868 (Python) # See links.
%Y A394868 Cf. A081350 (if both players want to maximize the number of steps).
%K A394868 nonn,more,new
